{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02442/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02442"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:24:42"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, tilt"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A pair of hands hooks together a corset."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02442","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02442"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1/a97c4d88-e26d-487e-a1aa-0f3701cb244f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:45:09.943Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The hook and eye fastener is frequently deployed in corsetry and supportive garments. Though depicting an act of dressing, we might read this shot, with its repeated insertion of the phallic hook into the open eye, as something of an erotic gesture in accordance with the film’s allusive approach to sex.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:607.2678331090175,300.32301480484523,562.0457604306865,240.32301480484523"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1/fc17f922-649c-4463-a4f8-df2e2ebec3df","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:45:48.377Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This scene is all about control. Reynolds makes claims about how he will give shape to Alma’s body depending on his preferences and desires. The process of “capturing” Alma, his newfound muse, through these hooks signifies his attempts to place her under his control.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1074.993270524899,89.71736204576045,355.31628532974446,191.22476446837146"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1/fce3d29a-89e4-4731-846a-1a4f3ec4c51d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:46:10.359Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Traditionally, the act of dressing another person would be a very subservient one, for the very wealthy a task literally completed by a servant. Reynolds tries to flip this dynamic, making dressing Alma an act of control. However, the submissive connotations foreshadow their later dynamic.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02442/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:71.06325706594899,40.619111709286884,324.3068640646029,337.2274562584118"}}}]}]}]}